&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM FOR 12 MONTHS TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job advert for Motiv8 project worker&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a dynamic project worker to work for Motiv8, a community based mental health charity which supports service users in engaging in activities to help maintain and improve their mental health. This post will be based predominately in the ICAN centres in Llandudno and Rhyl but will work closely with the Conwy Community Mental Health Occupational Therapy Team. This is an exciting opportunity for the post holder to set up a new service. The successful candidate will require experience in working with service users with mental health needs in the community and have their own transport to travel across Conwy and Denbighshire. The post holder needs to be able to work well within a team but also be confident and competent to work autonomously. The successful candidate will carry out group and individual interventions and be able to participate in a wide range of activities. The post holder will have effective interpersonal and communication skills, be motivated and confident to produce reports and have skills in project management . They will be also have excellent IT skills, and be competent in using online resources and social media.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 15 November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mark Morris&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Advanced Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 03000 850 049&lt;/p&gt;
